    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for a high-ceiling performance tonight, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.27). **Gunnar Henderson** is our clear priority play; he benefits from a premier hitting environment with a +16% park factor adjustment and a favorable matchup against Roupp. His top-of-the-order status, combined with a 14% boost from platoon splits, makes him the engine of our attack. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (75.13) warrants an elite designation against Rocker, where his strong xwOBA and high-leverage lineup slot provide a stable floor for our Roto categories. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (68.14) carries a slightly lower score due to platoon drag, his consistent contact metrics remain essential for our RBI production.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was leaving **Luis Robert Jr.** (44.27) on the bench. Despite his high base projection, his efficiency is severely hampered by a challenging matchup against Ginn and significant platoon regression. While his elite sprint speed and the opponent's slow delivery typically move the needle in our SB-starved format, the aggregate score couldn\u2019t overcome the strength of our starting outfielders. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Josh Lowe** (48.80) and **Heliot Ramos** (57.57); while both occupy favorable spots for speed-based upside, they face stiff competition today. **Josh Lowe** specifically faces a high-risk scenario against Burns, whose low xERA demands caution. Investors should note that **Marcell Ozuna** (58.49) remains a high-value UTIL play, capitalizing on park factors despite a tough draw against a talented lefty in Imanaga.",
